            As O&G Digital Senior Staff Analytics Advocate located at the Oil & Gas Technology Center (OGTC) in Oklahoma City you will work with the O&G Digital team and the OGTC Digital Leader to drive the development, adoption and usage of industrial analytics.  You will work with customers to understand product needs, and with engineers, data scientists and developers to create technical specifications for analytic prototypes to be integrated into products that address the customer requirements.
             The OGTC is GE O&G’s research division developing the next generation digital industrial technologies for product offerings spanning the OGTC program areas of Reservoir Performance, Well Construction & Production Solutions, and Oilfield Facilities & Services.  As Senior Staff Analytics Advocate, you will:
             Lead analytics framework development, working closely with analytics researchers, data scientists, mechanical, electrical, petroleum and chemical engineers
             Work with Product Managers and technical staff in customer engagements to understand user needs and define requirements for the analytics development and productization
             Develop technical specifications, implementation plan and productization plan for developing and validating analytics
             Work with analytics development, product strategy & product management teams to conceptualize new analytics products and features.
             Build connections with stakeholders in the GE Oil & Gas business and represent the OGTC with customers and industry associations.
             Provide technical support to sales and marketing teams for evangelizing industrial analytics products.
             Serve as a thought leader externally and internally, providing guidance on best practices, industry trends, and future potential for industrial analytics.
             Be able to influence from both a strategic and technical standpoint across the function and business. Ability to influence at the peer and senior leadership level is critical.
